ans, (he's not terribly charming is he? What I admire about many truly great leaders is how they win hearts without arousing resentment, he seems pretty devoid of that gift.)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
We don't wanna hear it. He's our boy, and he's a charming genius, with wisdom to spare to teach lessons to pretenders like Ghandi and Mother Theresa.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :puke --><img src=http://www.smilies-world.de/Smilies/Smilies_klein_1/puke.gif ALT=":puke"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
Excuse me... had to get that out. (&quot;gulp&quot;)<br>
<br>
 I've been greeting people with the raised right hand and &quot;Hail Bush, warlord, supreme leader of freedom around the world&quot;. About half have corrected me &quot;that's Heil...&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&gt; As far as civil liberties disappearing, where is it happening? What groups of people are having their civil rights stripped? Who is being put in jail for speaking their minds? The idea that the &quot;Dept of Homeland Security&quot; is out to take away the Bill of Rights from American citizens is as boneheaded and bogus as the right wing nuts thinking the UN planted secret messages on the back of stop signs back in the 90s.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Earlier I wrote:<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&gt; anyone who thinks the attacks on the bill of rights will only ever be used on viable terrorist suspects, is too naive to be believed, Such power will fight to stay entrenched, and it will be used for frivolous political gains. Every bit of history says so.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;If you're not outraged, then you're not paying attention&quot;<br>
<br>
enough said (and I know of professors and exchange students who have had their careers and studies interrupted by being deported unless they account for paperwork errors in the State Dept bureaucracy 5 years ago.)<br>
<br>
